Project: NoteFlow (Expo + React Native + TypeScript)

Goals:
- Build a performant, typed mobile app with notes, checklists, and ideas.
- Keep architecture simple, scalable, and consistent with Expo Router.

Tech Stack:
- Expo SDK 54
- React Native + TypeScript (strict)
- Expo Router (file-based navigation)
- Zustand + AsyncStorage persist middleware
- React Native Paper (MD3 theming)
- FlashList for long lists
- Zod for form validation

Folder Conventions:
- app/: routes and screens only
- components/: presentational reusable components
- store/: Zustand stores and state logic
- types/: domain interfaces and type guards
- constants/: theme tokens and constants
- docs/: architecture and technical docs

Code Style:
- Prefer explicit TypeScript types and no any.
- Use type guards for union types.
- Keep components focused; move heavy logic to store/utilities.
- Avoid deeply nested JSX and duplicated logic.
- Follow predictable naming: PascalCase for components, camelCase for vars/functions.

Performance Rules:
- Use FlashList for collections.
- Provide estimatedItemSize in every FlashList.
- Avoid unnecessary state in list rows.
- Use selectors with Zustand to prevent broad re-renders.

Architecture Constraints:
- Do not place business logic inside UI-only components.
- Keep persistence inside store middleware layer.
- Use Tabs for top-level sections, Stack for detail, modal for create flows.
- Respect dark/light mode tokens from constants/theme.ts.

Validation & UX:
- Validate inputs with Zod before store writes.
- Show user-facing validation messages near the field.
- Use haptics only for meaningful actions (delete/complete).
